        <div class="tab-content active" id="problem">
            <div class="card">
                <h2><i class="fas fa-exclamation-circle"></i> Problem Statement</h2>
                <p>Traditional workspace models fail to meet the needs of modern professionals, creating significant inefficiencies:</p>
                
                <div class="grid">
                    <div class="value-card">
                        <h4>Space Inefficiency</h4>
                        <p>40% of commercial space sits empty during business hours<span class="source">(JLL Research, 2023)</span></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="value-card">
                        <h4>High Costs</h4>
                        <p>Traditional office space costs businesses ₹15,000-₹25,000 per employee annually<span class="source">(CBRE, 2023)</span></p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="value-card">
                        <h4>Lack of Flexibility</h4>
                        <p>82% of freelancers report difficulty finding affordable, professional workspaces<span class="source">(FlexJobs Survey, 2023)</span></p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <h3>Current Solutions Fall Short</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Traditional co-working spaces require long-term commitments and are often centrally located, increasing commute times</li>
                    <li>Remote work leads to isolation and reduced collaboration</li>
                    <li>Cafés and home offices lack professional infrastructure and networking opportunities</li>
                    <li>Existing solutions don't effectively utilize the 15M+ sq ft of underutilized commercial space in Bengaluru alone<span class="source">(Knight Frank Research)</span></li>
                </ul>
                
                <h3>Environmental Impact</h3>
                <p>Daily commuting contributes significantly to urban carbon emissions, with the average professional generating 2.5 tons of CO2 annually from travel alone<span class="source">(CEEW Study, 2023)</span>.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        
